01:56:21,441 --> 01:56:25,969
I want something more than I've
ever wanted anything before.

1619
01:56:26,045 --> 01:56:28,809
I want to bring
Mrs. Threadgoode...

1620
01:56:28,881 --> 01:56:31,076
to our home.

1621
01:56:31,150 --> 01:56:33,778
I want her
to live here with us.

1622
01:56:33,853 --> 01:56:36,344
I want to give her the love
she's given me.

1623
01:56:36,422 --> 01:56:40,586
[Snicker] You're kiddin' me,
aren't you? I'm absolutely serious.

1624
01:56:40,660 --> 01:56:45,495
That's why I'm puttin' the
wall to Kyle's room back up.

1625
01:56:45,565 --> 01:56:48,625
Well, honey, this isn't
something you're just go and do.

1626
01:56:48,701 --> 01:56:51,363
I mean,
she's an old woman.

1627
01:56:51,437 --> 01:56:54,668
What if she got sick?
Who's gonna take care of her?

1628
01:56:54,741 --> 01:56:56,436
I will!

1629
01:56:56,509 --> 01:56:58,500
I can't leave her
in that place.

1630
01:56:58,578 --> 01:57:02,480
She's not a stray cat.
Hell, she isn't even family.

1631
01:57:02,548 --> 01:57:05,608
She's family to me.
Now, Evelyn.

1632
01:57:06,452 --> 01:57:09,512
<i>Evelyn?</i>

1633
01:57:09,589 --> 01:57:11,454
<i>Honey?</i>

1634
01:57:11,524 --> 01:57:13,515
<i>Ah, look...</i>

1635
01:57:13,593 --> 01:57:17,825
have you mentioned this
harebrained idea to her?

1636
01:57:17,897 --> 01:57:20,957
Not yet.
Well, good!

1637
01:57:21,034 --> 01:57:23,502
Then we'll just pretend
it never happened.

1638
01:57:23,569 --> 01:57:26,595
I'm making my own money.
I'll pay for everything.

1639
01:57:26,672 --> 01:57:30,233
You don't have to do
a thing.

1640
01:57:30,309 --> 01:57:32,800
Evelyn...

1641
01:57:32,879 --> 01:57:35,347
it's never
gonna happen.

1642
01:57:35,415 --> 01:57:38,077
So just forget
about it.

1643
01:57:39,685 --> 01:57:42,449
Don't you ever
say "never" to me.

1644
01:57:51,397 --> 01:57:54,195
Someone helped put a mirror
up in front of my face,

1645
01:57:54,267 --> 01:57:56,861
and I didn't like
what I saw one bit.

1646
01:57:56,936 --> 01:58:00,770
You know what I did?
I changed.

1647
01:58:00,840 --> 01:58:04,742
And that someone...
was Mrs. Threadgoode.

1648
01:58:04,811 --> 01:58:09,305
She needs my love and care,
and I'm gonna give it to her.

1649
01:58:11,084 --> 01:58:14,713
If you'll excuse me,
I have to go to the gym.

1650
01:58:19,659 --> 01:58:22,685
And if you won't listen
to reason...

1651
01:58:22,762 --> 01:58:26,391
there's always Towanda.

1652
01:58:41,180 --> 01:58:44,149
Hey, Nin...

1653
01:58:46,819 --> 01:58:49,845
What are you doing?

1654
01:58:49,922 --> 01:58:52,652
Those are her things,
Mrs. Threadgoode's things!

1655
01:58:52,725 --> 01:58:55,819
What are you doing in here?
Where's Mrs. Threadgoode? Who?

1656
01:58:55,895 --> 01:58:58,728
Mrs. Threadgoode! The woman
who lives here. Are you deaf?

1657
01:58:58,798 --> 01:59:01,699
I'm sorry, miss.
All they told me...

1658
01:59:01,767 --> 01:59:05,965
was that the woman who lived
in here died this morning.

1659
01:59:07,840 --> 01:59:09,967
Oh, my God!

1660
01:59:10,042 --> 01:59:14,376
Wha... What
are you sayin'?

1661
01:59:14,447 --> 01:59:16,608
<i>She died early
this morning.</i>

1662
01:59:16,682 --> 01:59:21,016
<i>They were shorthanded so they asked
me to take all this stuff down.</i>

1663
01:59:21,087 --> 01:59:23,578
<i>That's all I know.</i>

1664
01:59:42,975 --> 01:59:44,909
Stop that!

1665
01:59:44,977 --> 01:59:47,343
What is the matter
with you people?

1666
01:59:47,413 --> 01:59:50,348
Can't you wait a goddamn day,
for Chrissake?

1667
01:59:50,416 --> 01:59:53,408
Do you have no respect?
These are her things!

1668
01:59:53,486 --> 01:59:57,650
I'm sorry, but they told me to get
this room ready for another patient.

1669
01:59:57,723 --> 02:00:00,920
She may be just
another patient to you,

1670
02:00:00,993 --> 02:00:05,089
but she was my friend,
and I loved her. I'm sorry.

1671
02:00:05,164 --> 02:00:07,098
I'm just
following orders.

1672
02:00:07,166 --> 02:00:10,101
What is going on? Why
didn't you call me?

1673
02:00:10,169 --> 02:00:13,502
You could've called me before
you sent that idiot... I'm sorry.

1674
02:00:13,573 --> 02:00:16,235
It never occurred to me that
you would take it this hard.

1675
02:00:16,309 --> 02:00:19,938
I didn't even get to tell
her good-bye. Oh, I know.

1676
02:00:20,012 --> 02:00:23,971
These things are difficult, but
she died peacefully in her sleep.

1677
02:00:24,050 --> 02:00:27,315
To tell you the truth, I thought
you'd be happy for Mrs. Threadgoode.

1678
02:00:27,386 --> 02:00:30,412
Happy? Why, yes! This
is what she wanted.

1679
02:00:30,489 --> 02:00:32,423
What?
To be dead?

1680
02:00:32,491 --> 02:00:35,016
No, to go home.
You just missed her.

1681
02:00:35,094 --> 02:00:37,528
She left in a yellow cab
about a half hour ago.

1682
02:00:37,597 --> 02:00:40,293
I don't understand.
What? A cab?

1683
02:00:40,366 --> 02:00:44,632
She said there wasn't no reason for
her to stay now that Mrs. Otis had died.

1684
02:00:44,704 --> 02:00:47,332
Mrs...

1685
02:00:47,406 --> 02:00:49,567
Otis is dead?

1686
02:00:49,642 --> 02:00:53,510
Oh, Mrs. Otis died.

1687
02:00:53,579 --> 02:00:55,570
Mrs. Otis died!

1688
02:00:55,648 --> 02:00:58,845
Mrs. Otis!
Oh, God!

1689
02:00:58,918 --> 02:01:02,945
Not that... I'm glad that
Mrs. Otis died, it's just...

1690
02:01:03,022 --> 02:01:05,650
Oh, God,
I've gotta stop her.

1691
02:01:45,097 --> 02:01:48,328
Hey, Evelyn,
somebody stole my house.

1692
02:01:48,401 --> 02:01:51,302
It was right here
when I left.

1693
02:01:51,370 --> 02:01:56,137
Unless... Oh, Evelyn, you
don't reckon I'm crazy, do you?

1694
02:01:56,208 --> 02:02:00,406
It was here when I left.
No, honey, you're not crazy.

1695
02:02:00,479 --> 02:02:03,243
This is the place.

1696
02:02:03,316 --> 02:02:07,343
Why would anyone want to
steal an old lady's home?

1697
02:02:07,420 --> 02:02:09,547
Wasn't worth nothin'.

1698
02:02:09,622 --> 02:02:13,023
Oh, honey,
nobody stole it.

1699
02:02:13,092 --> 02:02:16,960
They had to tear it down.
It was condemned.

1700
02:02:17,029 --> 02:02:19,156
I'm sorry.
I shoulda told you.

1701
02:02:19,231 --> 02:02:22,496
Well, somebody
shoulda told me.

1702
02:02:22,568 --> 02:02:27,403
I'm old. I'm not a child. I'm sorry.

1703
02:02:27,473 --> 02:02:30,806
My husband Cleo and I
lived in this house...

1704
02:02:30,876 --> 02:02:33,367
for more than 40 years.

1705
02:02:33,446 --> 02:02:36,847
Now, it's... it's gone.

1706
02:02:36,916 --> 02:02:40,477
83 years worth of livin'
and all that's left of me...

1707
02:02:40,553 --> 02:02:44,580
is what's in this box, a
bunch of old cards and pictures.

1708
02:02:44,657 --> 02:02:47,125
Come on.
I'll take you home.

1709
02:02:47,193 --> 02:02:49,320
This is my home!

1710
02:02:49,395 --> 02:02:51,386
And now it's gone.

1711
02:02:51,464 --> 02:02:53,989
And Mrs. Otis
is gone.

1712
02:02:54,066 --> 02:02:56,159
I...

1713
02:02:56,235 --> 02:02:58,829
I don't quite
know what to do.

1714
02:02:58,904 --> 02:03:02,738
This is the first time I can remember
when I don't have a soul to look after.

1715
02:03:02,808 --> 02:03:05,174
You can come
look after me and Ed.

1716
02:03:05,244 --> 02:03:07,542
Oh, you're sweet,

1717
02:03:07,613 --> 02:03:10,411
but I think you're doin'
just fine on your own.

1718
02:03:10,483 --> 02:03:14,783
Don't you know you'd be
like a gift for us?

1719
02:03:14,854 --> 02:03:18,017
You're the reason
I get up every morning...

1720
02:03:18,090 --> 02:03:21,423
and that Mary Kay's
havin' such a good year...

1721
02:03:21,494 --> 02:03:26,056
and I don't look like some
blob from a horror movie.

1722
02:03:26,132 --> 02:03:30,159
Well, with a little help
from Idgie and Ruth.

1723
02:03:31,737 --> 02:03:34,262
Come on. I've got
your room all ready.

1724
02:03:34,340 --> 02:03:36,740
What does Ed say
about all this?

1725
02:03:36,809 --> 02:03:40,643
He'll learn
to love it.

1726
02:03:44,116 --> 02:03:48,246
Did I ever tell you that Mrs.
Otis was Sipsey's baby sister?

1727
02:03:48,320 --> 02:03:50,982
No, ma'am.
Yes, she was.

1728
02:03:51,056 --> 02:03:54,924
Mrs. Otis was with Sipsey
and me the night Sipsey died.

1729
02:03:54,994 --> 02:04:00,159
Sipsey told me a story that night
I've never told a living soul, Evelyn.

1730
02:04:00,232 --> 02:04:03,360
<i>A story about
what really happened...</i>

1731
02:04:03,436 --> 02:04:06,769
<i>the night Frank Bennett
disappeared.</i>

1732
02:04:31,063 --> 02:04:33,497
<i>[Applause, Whistling]</i>

1733
02:04:39,338 --> 02:04:42,865
Hey there! You got to come quick.

1734
02:04:42,942 --> 02:04:47,902
The show has hardly begun. You
got to come quick. You hear me?

1735
02:04:53,819 --> 02:04:56,413
Run, get help! Run,
quick! Where's the baby?

1736
02:04:56,489 --> 02:04:58,286
Never mind.

1737
02:05:00,526 --> 02:05:02,653
[Baby Crying]

1738
02:05:05,931 --> 02:05:08,866
[Crying]

1739
02:05:17,009 --> 02:05:18,670
Excuse me, sir.

1740
02:05:18,744 --> 02:05:24,239
I don't believe you should be
goin' anywhere with Ruth's baby.

1741
02:05:24,316 --> 02:05:27,080
<i>[Crying]</i>

1742
02:05:35,895 --> 02:05:38,625
Like I said,
you ain't goin' nowhere.

1743
02:05:38,697 --> 02:05:41,257
Damn, you a thickheaded
son-of-a-bitch, ain't you?

1744
02:05:45,471 --> 02:05:47,439
<i>I told you...</i>

1745
02:05:47,506 --> 02:05:51,943
you ain't goin' nowheres
with Miss Ruth's baby.

1746
02:05:52,011 --> 02:05:54,036
<i>[Crying]</i>

1747
02:05:57,583 --> 02:05:59,778
Come on, angel.
Come on.

1748
02:05:59,852 --> 02:06:03,686
Come on, sweetheart.
It's all right.

1749
02:06:03,756 --> 02:06:06,247
Come on.
It's all right, baby.

1750
02:06:09,161 --> 02:06:11,891
<i>[Idgie]
It was self-defense.</i>

1751
02:06:11,964 --> 02:06:16,799
I don't know why any white
jury would care why I did it.

1752
02:06:16,869 --> 02:06:19,667
Well, I saw it, and I can
testify. Excuse me here.

1753
02:06:19,738 --> 02:06:21,899
I don't mean
no offense here,

1754
02:06:21,974 --> 02:06:25,034
but I don't know who's less
likely to convince a jury,

1755
02:06:25,110 --> 02:06:27,374
my mama...
or Mr. Smokey.

1756
02:06:27,446 --> 02:06:30,244
No offense taken.

1757
02:06:30,316 --> 02:06:32,716
You're a good man,
Mr. Smokey.

1758
02:06:32,785 --> 02:06:36,812
You did good.
The sun's almost up.

1759
02:06:40,359 --> 02:06:43,726
George?
Mm-hmm?

1760
02:06:43,796 --> 02:06:46,560
I think...

1761
02:06:46,632 --> 02:06:50,159
it's hog-boiling time.

1762
02:06:50,235 --> 02:06:52,499
No, ma'am. It
ain't cold enough.

1763
02:06:52,571 --> 02:06:55,335
It's hog-boiling time.

1764
02:06:58,277 --> 02:07:00,211
<i>Big George?</i>

1765
02:07:00,279 --> 02:07:03,373
Uh-huh? When is that
barbecue gonna be ready?

1766
02:07:03,449 --> 02:07:05,781
It's gonna be ready
any time now.

1767
02:07:05,851 --> 02:07:10,754
Smells so damn good I just
can't wait to get me some.

1768
02:07:10,823 --> 02:07:15,123
Now, don't you forget to call
me when that's ready. All right.

1769
02:07:28,874 --> 02:07:31,138
Here you go.

1770
02:07:32,711 --> 02:07:36,340
Miss Idgie? Smokey left town. Yeah?

1771
02:07:36,415 --> 02:07:40,408
I thought it'd be best
under the circumstances.

1772
02:07:40,486 --> 02:07:44,445
He asked that
you tell Ruth good-bye.

1773
02:07:44,523 --> 02:07:46,991
Shame he had to go.

1774
02:07:53,966 --> 02:07:58,869
<i>[Knocking]
Hold on! I'm comin'.</i>

1775
02:08:03,742 --> 02:08:06,506
What you want?
We want some barbecue.

1776
02:08:06,578 --> 02:08:10,275
Not today you don't.
Go on.

1777
02:08:23,328 --> 02:08:26,456
Why, this is about the
best barbecue I ever ate!

1778
02:08:27,966 --> 02:08:31,458
The secret's
in the sauce.

1779
02:08:40,245 --> 02:08:44,113
Sipsey?
My God!

1780
02:08:44,183 --> 02:08:48,517
That fryin' pan did more
than fry chicken that night.

1781
02:08:50,289 --> 02:08:54,749
Did Idgie really barbecue Frank
Bennett? Are you pullin' my leg?

1782
02:08:54,827 --> 02:08:58,524
Secret's in the sauce,
or so I've been told.

1783
02:09:02,034 --> 02:09:05,868
Now you know why
Idgie had to go on trial.

1784
02:09:05,938 --> 02:09:09,567
She knew the law would never
believe Sipsey. No!

1785
02:09:09,641 --> 02:09:12,132
Sipsey or Big George
or anyone else of color...

1786
02:09:12,211 --> 02:09:15,669
would've been hangin'
from the nearest tree.

1787
02:09:15,748 --> 02:09:18,012
To this day,
I'm still not sure...

1788
02:09:18,083 --> 02:09:20,643
whether Ruth
ever believed...

1789
02:09:20,719 --> 02:09:24,849
that Idgie didn't kill
Frank Bennett.

1790
02:09:24,923 --> 02:09:29,155
Truth's a funny thing
sometimes.

1791
02:09:29,228 --> 02:09:33,187
I feel better now.
Good.

1792
02:09:33,265 --> 02:09:36,564
I feel better 'cause
all these people'll live...

1793
02:09:36,635 --> 02:09:39,695
as long as
you remember 'em.

1794
02:09:39,772 --> 02:09:41,706
You reminded me...

1795
02:09:41,774 --> 02:09:45,175
about what the most
important thing in life is.

1796
02:09:45,244 --> 02:09:47,576
Do you know what I
think it is? No, ma'am.

1797
02:09:47,646 --> 02:09:50,911
Friends.
Best friends.

1798
02:09:50,983 --> 02:09:54,009
Oh, Ninny!

1799
02:09:55,187 --> 02:09:56,916
Look.

1800
02:10:02,194 --> 02:10:04,025
Oh!

1801
02:10:23,248 --> 02:10:25,182
Idgie?

1802
02:10:28,654 --> 02:10:32,522
<i>Idgie's alive?
Oh, yes!</i>

1803
02:10:32,591 --> 02:10:36,857
She's still out and about
charmin' bees and selling honey.

1804
02:10:36,929 --> 02:10:40,888
Sometimes I think
I catch a glimpse of her.

1805
02:10:46,805 --> 02:10:49,239
Maybe we'll
see her today.

1806
02:10:49,308 --> 02:10:51,936
Maybe.

1807
02:10:53,612 --> 02:10:56,308
Let's go.

1808
02:11:07,826 --> 02:11:12,126
<i>[Ninny] After Ruth died and
the railroad stopped runnin',</i>

1809
02:11:12,197 --> 02:11:16,190
<i>the cafe shut down, and everybody
Just scattered to the winds.</i>

1810
02:11:17,536 --> 02:11:20,903
<i>It was never more than just
a little knockabout place.</i>

1811
02:11:20,973 --> 02:11:23,771
<i>But now that
I look back on it,</i>

1812
02:11:23,842 --> 02:11:26,106
<i>when that cafe closed...</i>

1813
02:11:26,178 --> 02:11:30,274
<i>the heart of the town
Just stopped beating.</i>

1814
02:11:30,349 --> 02:11:33,182
<i>It's funny how
a little place like this...</i>

1815
02:11:33,252 --> 02:11:37,086
<i>brought so
many people together.</i>

1816
02:12:21,233 --> 02:12:25,693
<i>["I'll Remember You"
Performed by Grayson Hugh]</i>

1817
02:12:32,277 --> 02:12:35,178
<i>I'll remember you</i>

1818
02:12:37,816 --> 02:12:42,014
<i>When I've forgotten
all the rest</i>

1819
02:12:44,690 --> 02:12:48,490
<i>You to me
were true</i>

1820
02:12:50,762 --> 02:12:54,323
<i>You to me
were the best</i>

1821
02:12:55,634 --> 02:12:58,933
<i>When there is no more</i>

1822
02:12:59,004 --> 02:13:01,802
<i>You cut to the core</i>

1823
02:13:03,241 --> 02:13:08,269
<i>Quicker than anyone
that I knew</i>

1824
02:13:08,347 --> 02:13:12,477
<i>Now when the
roses fade</i>

1825
02:13:12,551 --> 02:13:16,487
<i>I'm in the shade
baby</i>

1826
02:13:16,555 --> 02:13:19,922
<i>I'll remember you</i>

1827
02:13:19,992 --> 02:13:23,985
<i>Now listen
didn't I</i>

1828
02:13:24,062 --> 02:13:28,089
<i>Didn't I love you</i>

1829
02:13:28,166 --> 02:13:34,537
<i>Didn't I
didn't I care</i>

1830
02:13:34,606 --> 02:13:40,567
<i>Didn't I sleep
and didn't I weep beside you</i>

1831
02:13:40,645 --> 02:13:45,981
<i>With the rain that
was blowing in your hair</i>

1832
02:13:46,051 --> 02:13:48,110
<i>Oh-oh-oh-oh-oh</i>

1833
02:13:49,221 --> 02:13:52,156
<i>I'll remember you</i>

1834
02:13:53,425 --> 02:13:55,655
<i>When the wind blows</i>

1835
02:13:55,727 --> 02:13:59,823
<i>On through
the piney wood</i>

1836
02:14:01,266 --> 02:14:07,671
<i>It was you who came
right through for me, baby</i>

1837
02:14:07,739 --> 02:14:11,368
<i>It was you
who understood</i>

1838
02:14:12,511 --> 02:14:15,742
<i>Though I'd never say</i>

1839
02:14:15,814 --> 02:14:20,683
<i>That I turned the way</i>

1840
02:14:20,752 --> 02:14:25,314
<i>That you
have led me to</i>

1841
02:14:25,390 --> 02:14:29,326
<i>Darling, in the end</i>

1842
02:14:29,394 --> 02:14:33,524
<i>My dear sweet friend</i>

1843
02:14:33,598 --> 02:14:36,897
<i>I'll remember you</i>

1844
02:14:36,968 --> 02:14:40,563
<i>Yes, I will now</i>

1845
02:14:40,639 --> 02:14:43,233
<i>I'll remember you</i>

1846
02:14:43,308 --> 02:14:45,606
<i>Yes, I will now</i>

1847
02:14:47,913 --> 02:14:51,314
